<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Married At First Sight star Jules Robinson has revealed she's 'struggling to walk' after gaining 17.5kg during her pregnancy.</p>

<p>The 37-year-old shared a series of photos and a post about her journey to Instagram on Wednesday, ahead of the arrival of her first child with husband Cameron Merchant.</p>

<p>'As the end is near...well actually the start of new beginnings. I think back to when my bump was so little, but to me it was so big,' she wrote.</p>

<p>Journey: MAFS' Jules Robinson has revealed she's gained 17.5kg during her pregnancy and is struggling to walk as she counts down the final days until she welcomes her first child</p>

<p>'Fast forward to photo three and 17.5 kilos heavier and yep the struggle is real. I can only just walk by night, it's more of a slide,' she added.</p>

<p>She also said the most important thing is her 'growing baby is health as that's all that matters'.</p>

<p>Happy and healthy: She also said the most important thing is her 'growing baby is health as that is all that matters'</p>

<p>Jules continued to say that she's looking forward to getting back to fitting into all her dresses after giving birth.</p>

<p>'I will do just that, with no pressure on my self or my body... I look forward to feeling fit and strong but most importantly becoming a healthy and happy mum to my little one,' she said.</p>

<p>Jules is currently 39 weeks pregnant and expecting her little one any day now.</p>

<p>Not long to go! Jules is currently 39 weeks pregnant and expecting her little one any day now</p>

<p>Earlier this month, Cameron shared a photo of the sonogram of the baby while Jules was getting an ultrasound.</p>

<p>'Coming soon to a world near you,' Cameron wrote, referencing his unborn child.</p>

<p>'Not sure if you can see but I'm actually smiling ear to ear.'</p>

<p> Soon! Earlier this month, Cameron shared a photo of the sonogram of the baby while Jules was getting an ultrasound</p>
